      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions used to verify solver accuracy for linear static structural analysis at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical was verified against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 and LE10 linear elastic test cases. Computed displacements and stresses agreed with reference solutions to within 0.3%, satisfying Gradation 2 numerical code verification requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between successive refinements; discretization error quantified and reported.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the pedicle screw-rod construct model. Construct stiffness and yield force QoIs changed by less than 1.4% between the medium and fine meshes. The production mesh (approximately 280,000 elements, C3D10 tetrahedral) was selected based on convergence criteria, satisfying Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Default solver tolerances documented; residual norms reported to confirm solution convergence.",
      "rationale": "Linear static analysis with direct sparse solver. Force and displacement residuals converged to machine precision. No iterative solver tolerance issues identified. Gradation 1 requirement satisfied."
