      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material assignments verified against documented model setup checklist.",
      "rationale": "An independent FDA analyst reviewed all model inputs, boundary conditions (fixed inferior vertebral body, axial compressive load at superior body per ASTM F1717), and material assignments against the documented setup checklist. No use errors identified. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model and contact formulation justified by literature and validated against independent test data; simplifying assumptions documented and sensitivity assessed.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive model for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) justified by manufacturer material certificates and literature. Frictional contact between screw and rod with coefficient 0.2 validated against independent torque-to-tighten measurements. Simplifying assumptions (rigid vertebral body surrogates, no thread engagement detail) documented; sensitivity analysis confirmed <5% QoI sensitivity to these assumptions. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs derived from traceable measurements; input uncertainty quantified and propagated to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) sourced from DePuy Synthes material certificates traceable to ASTM F136. Screw geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production implants (n=5). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (n=1000 runs); combined input uncertainty contributed uval = 3.2% to stiffness QoI. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens are production-representative implants; lot traceability documented; sufficient sample size (N≥10) to characterize experimental variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-lot implants with full lot traceability documentation. Specimens distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability. Sample size satisfies Gradation 3 requirements for characterizing experimental scatter in QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. Although this configuration is the regulatory standard, only one load condition was evaluated, precluding assessment of condition-to-condition variability. This factor achieves Gradation 2 rather than the required Gradation 3. The shortfall is acknowledged; the accepted overall credibility reflects compensating strength in all other factors and the direct regulatory relevance of the F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs match experimental specimen measurements; any discrepancies between nominal and measured values quantified and their effect on QoIs assessed.",
      "rationale": "Model geometry updated to match CMM-measured screw and rod dimensions for each of the 11 test specimens. Applied load and boundary conditions replicated the test machine configuration. Discrepancies between nominal and as-built dimensions were <0.05 mm; sensitivity analysis confirmed negligible effect (<1%) on QoIs. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoIs; E/uval < 1.96 for each QoI; percentage difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for construct stiffness (0.87), yield force (1.12), and force at 40 mm displacement (1.31). All values below the 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences were 4.2%, 6.8%, and 5.5% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound. Gradation 3 output comparison requirements satisfied across all three QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes of interest; linkage to COU decision explicitly documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Each QoI maps directly to a clinical failure mode (excessive flexibility, permanent deformation, gross fracture). Gradation 3 relevance satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
