      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions are representative of the intended COU; any differences between validation and COU contexts are documented and their impact assessed.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry, ASTM F1717 test configuration, and production-representative specimens as the intended COU submission. The FEA framework validated here is applied without modification to the submission prediction. No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required. Gradation 3 relevance of validation activities to COU satisfied."
